description:
**The Job in Short**



We're looking for a skilled UX/UI designer to strengthen our design team in Backbase Retail Banking Value Stream across mobile and web experiences.


**Meet the Job**



As part of the BB design team, you will work closely with UX research, product and engineering teams, with the purpose of working leaner and more collaboratively to bring the value of your work to light faster. Your role will also focus on considering the entire customer journey when carrying out design discovery and implementation, to ensure a more intuitive and wholistic experience for the end user.



Most importantly, you will be the voice of the user at Backbase. You'll need to be passionate about understanding what businesses want from their banks both now and in the future. We are looking for designers who are well versed in the entire design process and how financial banking products can better help businesses.



We have a great, creative culture in the overall design team with over 90 UI/UX designers and researchers working across the organization.




**How about you?**


* Do you think you would be a great addition to the Retail Banking team, bringing your creativity, passion and experience with you? Then please note the requirements below.
* Between 3-5 years experience designing UI/UX for web and mobile applications;
* Have worked with complex info-heavy products and interactions (e.g. forms, data, workflows) and thrive in data visualization;
* A strong understanding of design and developments guidelines for both web and mobile platforms;
* A strong understanding of interactive design fundamentals;
* Strong visual design skills to create clear yet beautiful designs;
* Figma as your tool of choice;
* Be passionate and a fierce advocate for best-practice design methodologies and technologies;
* A goal to work in the fintech space, and bonus points if you already have experience here;
* A strong online portfolio demonstrating your work, please include the link in your resume. We love to see the entire end-to-end process of your work!

**The Job in Short**
--------------------



Lead the User Research projects and operations for Business Banking at Backbase, serving multiple global products.


**Meet the Job**
----------------



This is an exciting role in a specialist team of 8 dedicated UX Researchers. You'll work across the full spectrum of product and feature development, from concepts to delivery while answering some of the most challenging questions in FinTech.



Backbase is at the centre of a global transformation in Digital Banking, recently ranked #1 by Forrester and Gartner for digital banking platforms. You'll have the unique opportunity to research and test within our established Business Banking product line. We are continuously improving our current offering of products and features for micro to medium sized businesses as well as that we're optimising that what already exists for them.



You'll conduct primary research; exploring the experiences, behaviours, and needs of our users, and then work with teams of designers, Product Managers, engineers and others to create and build intuitive, innovative, and beautiful products that people love to use. Most importantly, you will be the voice of the user at Backbase. You'll need to be passionate about understanding what banks' users need, both now and in the future. Methods employed will include employed will be both qualitative and quantitative, ranging from surveys to in-depth interviews and unmoderated usability testing.



We have a great, creative culture in our UX Guild with over 70 UI/UX Designers and Researchers working across our Product Development department. We are looking for someone who will be a great addition to this team, bringing creativity, passion, and solid research experience.



While Amsterdam is HQ for Backbase, being onsite with our customers and meeting the users is essential. We work with our customers in Europe, North and South America, South Africa, Russia and the Middle East, so when Covid restrictions allow for it - you'll get the chance to travel!


**How about you?**
------------------



Are you passionate about your end customer where you can bring user centred design to the heart of the product teams to ensure our customers have the best banking experiences?



As a Senior UX Researcher, you are independently driving the research roadmap and research projects within the Business Banking domain. You are advising the product teams as well as product management on research priorities as well as mentoring more junior researchers in their endeavours. To do this, we think you will need to:  

* Have 5 years of experience conducting user research within a UX team for software/digital products;
* You are well able to identify and prioritise research objectives across various product teams. You are able to defend those priorities and communicate about those in a clear and transparent way;
* You love to teach and educate other researchers as well as designers on how to set-up and run solid and valid user research;
* You understand what good quality research work looks like and are able to deliver on those standards consistently;
* You know how to drive research maturity - and you're able to identify opportunities that bring the research discipline forward and can make relevant initiatives happen;
* You have a Bachelors and/or Master's Degree in the study of user experience, design, research, business or related fields; for example, Information Design, Human Factors/HCI, Psychology, Cognitive Sciences;
* You have demonstrated knowledge of user-centred design principles and practices; such as design thinking and service design;
* You have hands-on experience with variety of qualitative research methodologies: including in-person and remote moderated one-on-one sessions, card sorting, contextual inquiry, and usability studies.


Some added bonus points if you have experience:  

* Having experience in financial applications/services, marketing campaign and content management tools and complex user journeys is highly desirable;
* Managing and recruiting suitable and representative groups of respondents;
* Developing and executing research with users of Clients/Customers (B2B2B);
* You have experience advocating research findings and empathy to diverse audiences through written reports and presentations;
* You have experience incorporating complex technical and business requirements into research;
* You have working knowledge in guiding teams or customers in taking decisions that align with research insights.
